association_orig: 28-32, associate it with going letterboxing (or geocaching)
description_orig: Going with friends and family to find a letterbox for my sister's birthday.
description_cover: Driving down the road to the grocery store and singing along with the song.
experience_orig: I remember being in a car with my sister and her friends for her birthday on the way to go letterboxing (geocaching) and they would sing along to it when it came on. We went and found multiple letterboxes/geocaches and the song would come on frequently and they sang each time.
experience_cover: I remember driving to the grocery store in the summer with my windows down signing along to this song. It's still very catchy. I listen to it sometimes on spotify or pandora and when it came out I watched the video for the song often on youtube.

description_cover: I remember listening to the song on the radio as I drove to the dentist to have a tooth pulled.
experience_orig: It played often and was an ear worm, but I remember it most from listening to it while driving to get a tooth pulled at the dentist. I think it played twice on the somewhat short drive to the dentist which is probably why I remember it. When I hear the song now I think back to that time so I don't really like the song.
experience_cover: Heard the song often on the radio but never loved it, but it is an earworm. I would hear it multiple times while driving in car.

association_cover: It's connected with my studying for the GRE and going back to school.

experience_orig: I really liked the hook of this song and I remember listening to it often. I remember talking with my sister about it while we ate at an IHOP and studied GRE vocab words.  It was on my spotify/pandora playlists when it came out. It was my favorite song for a few months when it came out.
experience_cover: I remember loving the hook from the moment I heard it and then talking with my friends about it. I was a big "FUN" fan before they made it big so seeing them come out with this song was cool.
